Interface StaveInterface

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, NameableInterface, ReadOnlyNameableInterface
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BezierStave, BinaryPatternSteppingStave, ClosurePatternSteppingStave, ConstantStave, EdgeStave, IntervalStave, PatternSteppingStave, RampContinuousStave, RampSteppingStave, SinusStave, StaveAbstract, TriggerStave, ZeroStave

    public interface StaveInterface
extends NameableInterface, java.lang.Cloneable
    Stave Interface At the most abstract level, a stave has duration in time and knows the signal value at any point in normalized relative time [0,1].
    Author:
    Loic Royer (2015)
